 class=""><path d="M32 12.964v14.179c0 1.571-1.286 2.857-2.857 2.857h-26.286c-1.571 0-2.857-1.286-2.857-2.857v-14.179c0.536 0.589 1.143 1.107 1.804 1.554 2.964 2.018 5.964 4.036 8.875 6.161 1.5 1.107 3.357 2.464 5.304 2.464h0.036c1.946 0 3.804-1.357 5.304-2.464 2.911-2.107 5.911-4.143 8.893-6.161 0.643-0.446 1.25-0.964 1.786-1.554zM32 7.714c0 2-1.482 3.804-3.054 4.893-2.786 1.929-5.589 3.857-8.357 5.804-1.161 0.804-3.125 2.446-4.571 2.446h-0.036c-1.446 0-3.411-1.643-4.571-2.446-2.768-1.946-5.571-3.875-8.339-5.804-1.268-0.857-3.071-2.875-3.071-4.5 0-1.75 0.946-3.25 2.857-3.25h26.286c1.554 0 2.857 1.286 2.857 2.857z"></path> <a href="#" aria-label="Email" data-ss-ss-link="mailto:?body=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visualcapitalist.com%2Ffeed%2F&#038;subject=Visualized%3A%20The%20Price%20of%20Carbon%20Around%20the%20World%20in%202024" class="ss-envelope-color" rel="nofollow noopener" data-ss-ss-network-id="envelope" data-ss-ss-post-id="167802" data-ss-ss-location="inline_content" data-ss-ss-permalink="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/feed/" data-ss-ss-type="share"><span class="ss-share-network-content"><span class="ss-reveal-label-wrap"><span class="ss-network-label">电子邮件</span></span></span></a></li></ul></div></div><div class="vce-sponsor-disclaimer"><span class="vce-sponsor-disclaimer-text">以下内容由<a href="https://www.motive-power.com/national-public-utilities-council/?utm_source=decarb-channel&amp;utm_medium=sponsored-content&amp;utm_campaign=Decarbonization" class="vce-sponsor-disclaimer-link" target="_blank">国家公用事业委员会</a>赞助</span></div><div class="vce-full-width-viz"><a href="https://www.motive-power.com/national-public-utilities-council/?utm_source=decarb-channel&#038;utm_medium=sponsored-content&#038;utm_campaign=Decarbonization" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/NPUC24-8-carbon-price-around-the-world-20240620_Infographic.jpg" alt="条形图显示了世界银行数据中碳税最高和最低的经济体，并强调乌拉圭的碳税是世界上最高的。"></a> </div><div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-1 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex"><div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow" style="flex-basis:70%"><h2 class="wp-block-heading">可视化：世界各地碳的价格</h2><p>全球排放量中只有 1% 的定价足以满足《巴黎协定》2024 年的气温目标。</p><p>该图表是与<a href="https://www.motive-power.com/national-public-utilities-council/?utm_source=decarb-channel&amp;utm_medium=sponsored-content&amp;utm_campaign=Decarbonization" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">国家公共事业委员会</a>合作创建的，使用 <a href="https://carbonpricingdashboard.worldbank.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">世界银行</a>的数据显示了世界各地的碳价格。</p><p>让我们首先了解什么是碳定价及其运作方式。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">什么是碳定价？</h2><p>碳定价是一种环境策略，旨在通过为碳排放分配货币成本来减少温室气体排放。</p><p>最常见的碳定价类型是排放交易体系（ETS）和<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/ranking-the-top-15-countries-by-carbon-tax-revenue/">碳税</a>。前者设定总体排放限额并分配交易许可证，而后者则征收排放费以增加成本并激励减排。</p><p>根据世界银行的数据，<strong>芬兰和波兰</strong>是最早于 1990 年实施联邦碳定价的国家。另一方面，最近的国家是<strong>澳大利亚、匈牙利和印度尼西亚，</strong>于 2023 年实施碳定价。</p><h2 class="wp-block-heading">按地区划分的碳价格</h2><p>2017年，碳定价领导联盟建议，到2030年，碳价格应在<a href="https://static1.squarespace.com/static/54ff9c5ce4b0a53decccfb4c/t/59b7f26b3c91f1bb0de2e41a/1505227373770/CarbonPricing_EnglishSummary.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">50-100美元/tCO <sub>2</sub></a>之间，以满足《巴黎气候协议》的温度目标。</p><p>快进到 2024 年，全球平均碳价为 32 美元/tCO <sub>2</sub> — 比六年内所需的最低碳价低 18 美元。</p><p>不同地区的碳定价差异很大。欧洲和中亚是世界上定价举措数量最多的地区，<strong>平均价格为 50 美元/tCO <sub>2</sub></strong> 。</p><p>在美国和加拿大，平均价格略低，为每吨 48 美元，并采取了 16 项举措。北美方法的特点是联邦和州/省系统，包括加拿大联邦碳定价和美国区域温室气体倡议等著名计划。 </p><table id="tablepress-4407" class="tablepress tablepress-id-4407"><thead><tr class="row-1 odd"><th class="column-1">地区</th><th class="column-2">平均碳价</th><th class="column-3">倡议数量</th></tr></thead><tbody class="row-hover"><tr class="row-2 even"><td class="column-1">欧洲和中亚</td><td class="column-2">50 美元</td><td class="column-3">26</td></tr><tr class="row-3 odd"><td class="column-1">美国和加拿大</td><td class="column-2">48 美元</td><td class="column-3">16</td></tr><tr class="row-4 even"><td class="column-1">拉丁美洲和加勒比地区</td><td class="column-2">24 美元</td><td class="column-3">11</td></tr><tr class="row-5 odd"><td class="column-1">东亚及太平洋地区</td><td class="column-2">11 美元</td><td class="column-3">18</td></tr><tr class="row-6 even"><td class="column-1">非洲</td><td class="column-2">10 美元</td><td class="column-3">1</td></tr></tbody></table><!-- #tablepress-4407 from cache --><p>欧盟的 ETS 体系于 2005 年推出。该举措使 2022 年至 2023 年间涵盖的排放量<a href="https://climate.ec.europa.eu/news-your-voice/news/record-reduction-2023-ets-emissions-due-largely-boost-renewable-energy-2024-04-03_en#:~:text=The%20data%20reported%20by%20EU,2030%20target%20of%20%2D62%25." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">减少了 16%</a> ，创造了<a href="https://dev-rad-carbon-pricing.pantheonsite.io/compliance/revenue" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">470 亿美元的</a>收入。一些欧盟成员国还实施了自己的碳定价机制，以解决欧盟排放交易体系范围之外的部门问题或创造国内收入。</p><p>尽管欧洲、中亚和北美做出了显着的努力，但世界上最高的碳税属于<strong>乌拉圭，为 167 美元/tCO <sub>2</sub></strong> 。根据世界银行的数据，乌拉圭的人均GDP为20,795美元，明显低于其他实行《巴黎协定》碳定价的国家。</p><p>尽管采取了这些不同的举措，但全球平均碳价格仍然落后于实现《巴黎协定》目标可能所需的水平，这凸显出可能需要更强有力和更广泛地采用碳定价来推动有意义的气候行动。</p> <a class="vc-newsletter" href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/subscribe/"><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1216" src="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/footer-email.gif" alt="订阅视觉资本家" /></a> <div class="wpforms-container wpforms-container-full vc-subscribe-post" id="wpforms-140438"><form id="wpforms-form-140438" class="wpforms-validate wpforms-form wpforms-ajax-form" data-formid="140438" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data" action="/feed/" data-token="0dcc894b48555370b94e3eb45f18c495" data-token-time="1719331506"><noscript class="wpforms-error-noscript">请在您的浏览器中启用 JavaScript 以完成此表格。 </noscript><div class="wpforms-field-container"><div id="wpforms-140438-field_1-container" class="wpforms-field wpforms-field-email vc-subscribe-post-email" data-field-id="1"><label class="wpforms-field-label" for="wpforms-140438-field_1">喜欢上面的数据可视化吗？ <span class="wpforms-required-label">*</span></label> <input type="email" id="wpforms-140438-field_1" class="wpforms-field-large wpforms-field-required" name="wpforms[fields][1]" placeholder="Your email address" spellcheck="false" required></div></div><!-- .wpforms-field-container --><input type="hidden" name="wpforms_form_name" value="Post Bottom Subscribe" /><div class="wpforms-submit-container" ><input type="hidden" name="wpforms[id]" value="140438"><input type="hidden" name="page_title" value=""><input type="hidden" name="page_url" value="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/feed/"> <button type="submit" name="wpforms[submit]" id="wpforms-submit-140438" class="wpforms-submit vc-subscribe-post-button" data-alt-text="Sending..." data-submit-text="Subscribe" aria-live="assertive" value="wpforms-submit">订阅</button><img decoding="async" src="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/wp-content/plugins/wpforms/assets/images/submit-spin.svg" class="wpforms-submit-spinner" style="display: none;" width="26" height="26" alt="加载中"></div></form></div><!-- .wpforms-container --><div class="vc-related-posts"><span class="vc-tag-title">相关主题:</span> #<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/tag/greenhouse-gas-emissions/" rel="tag">温室气体排放</a>#<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/tag/motive-power-2/" rel="tag">动力</a>#<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/tag/carbon-tax/" rel="tag">碳税</a>#<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/tag/carbon-pricing/" rel="tag">碳定价</a>#<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/tag/partner/" rel="tag">合作伙伴</a>#<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/tag/carbon-price/" rel="tag">碳价格</a></div><div id="vc_comments" class="vc-comments-block"><div id="mvp-comments-button" class="left relative mvp-com-click"><span class="mvp-comment-but-text">点击评论</span></div><!--mvp-comments-button--><div id="disqus_thread" class="disqus-thread-16780